; 📌 1. MongoDB vs SQL (Core Difference)
; Feature	MongoDB	SQL
; Type	NoSQL	Relational
; Data	JSON (document)	Tables (rows)
; Schema	Flexible	Fixed
; Query	JS methods	SQL language
; 🔥 One Line

; MongoDB = flexible, SQL = structured

; 📌 2. Data Storage Difference
; 🔹 MongoDB
; { name: "Ajeet", age: 22 }
; 🔹 SQL
; id | name | age
; 1  | Ajeet | 22
; 📌 3. Relation Difference (Important 🔥)
; MongoDB	SQL
; ObjectId (ref)	Foreign Key
; populate()	JOIN
; 🔹 MongoDB
; userId: ObjectId("123")
; 🔹 SQL
; user_id REFERENCES users(id)
; 📌 4. Data Fetch Difference
; 🔹 MongoDB
; Post.find().populate("userId")
; 🔹 SQL
; SELECT * FROM posts
; JOIN users ON posts.user_id = users.id;
; 📌 5. Model Difference
; MongoDB Model	SQL Model
; Schema define	Query functions
; Built-in methods	Manual SQL
; Example: User.find()	SELECT * FROM users
; 📌 6. Controller Difference
; MongoDB	SQL
; Simple calls	Query handle
; Direct object	rows use
; Less code	More control
; 🔹 Mongo Controller
; const users = await User.find();
; 🔹 SQL Controller
; const users = await pool.query("SELECT * FROM users");
; 📌 7. Insert Difference
; MongoDB
; User.create(data);
; SQL
; INSERT INTO users ...
; 📌 8. Performance Thinking
; Case	MongoDB	SQL
; Flexible data	✅	❌
; Complex relations	❌	✅
; Fast nested read	✅	❌
; 📌 9. Token Flow (Same for both)
; Login → token → store → send → verify
; 📌 10. Key Mapping (Super Important 🔥)
; MongoDB	SQL
; Collection	Table
; Document	Row
; ObjectId	Primary Key
; ref	Foreign Key
; populate()	JOIN
; 🧠 Interview Golden Lines
; "MongoDB is schema-less, SQL is schema-based"
; "MongoDB uses documents, SQL uses tables"
; "populate is similar to JOIN"
; "SQL ensures data integrity using constraints"
; ⚡ Final 1 Minute Revision

; 👉 Mongo → flexible + fast dev
; 👉 SQL → structured + safe
; 👉 populate = JOIN
; 👉 Model ≠ Controller

; 🚀 Pro Line (Impress interviewer)

; "Choice between MongoDB and SQL depends on use case, scalability, and data relationships."

